        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 10:33AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1033 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Chesterton, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Winds to around 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Station, Chesterton, New Chicago, Portage, Town of Pines,
Porter, Dune Acres, Beverly Shores, Burns Harbor, Ogden Dunes, Gary,
and Hobart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
